5X6AKMOroM9P9oyDJTfyScDb1NZ9UnH5PqQYp-l7Y_M0F-oq6NuQxQFKoYmF0C9mbTDAFaTUCN6BkyrhkJ13LY16aEY1s2hmCJWbgMEGPktWtTm6f_fqPcf22moXjoBrnTZQVQ2v8sGpQ4uwDeWqJVnCpkybc9Gt2Vxrct3-11LiJO2AfRSZ1zaxL-9vJcAZBcfHtofvcXFnuVz7l-mzY9fHIpagLIbqOKkPxXyNsf2qi72hZJ5i4yr05KCC3o17WOQ_uNnJ8YYDKK1IRJE1VJ9j-CWv0EJVRQByjB0JS7ILKHQcWTsjlC2GdAbTl_iMOSm2DjDvJ2W84zMMkTFs6dopT_YiP_-5bPgRLFt6gELKUy_lizLq-1znghlY7x5HIqJ95lYantyxK0pbcZ7ngfNI-nkW99EhoU81BelxnW-2t_xp1QC-xNOlg6r_MI8-ovtazGdRJ2_0f6T8wPEZXcUVKA1RzTeD_skM4ASvOaCagndVR6pNpbQThpNsRGR7cd6pDlukH_myCGl9HHF_xvlxaDLVaQY5XEn4tykCducLcBkQgebuQETg34p3YiXG95gxs1s6ZvqQcMK1Rh2pVvmM9eBpIXAGDtNpaoRSV4PofgJiDL2IQe3s2svZV3m7SN0o_JIr9yKZBPc6KYHUI99gFIrE5Etlb1a68qmiWbUvDwfdYGamBb3GPvJIiZXq93um4I1LViRhZkiM7t2sTXDHvbtaQW8dsSnlXpJHv05u1FAP9myMnuVPSy_KOvWoIHxcIVp9k0nKJRPBersTdCGqJ2qWxh2H6tMmwDoY-l9lvU=\\\",\\\"summary\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering CompilerFactoryFactory report**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about creating a dynamic report for CompilerFactoryFactory. Wait, I wonder if it's really necessary for that task or if removing old elements will lead to stale metadata. That’s something I need to evaluate. It's important to ensure that everything is up to date and effective. I want to clarify that before moving forward, so the results are accurate and useful. Let’s explore this further before making any decisions!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Implementing TestCompilerFactory modifications**\\\\n\\\\nI need to make the existing TestCompilerFactory public and static final. I’ll override two methods and add the required import for AbstractJavaSourceClassLoader, which is similar to the current import for AbstractCompilerFactory. I’ll implement the newJavaSourceClassLoader methods accordingly. There's no issue with ICompiler; the new class package is already sanitized. I’m pondering whether the loader class should be public or nested—perhaps it can remain package-private.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolC