e new `AbstractJavaSourceClassLoaderTest`, which could allow for existing references. I wonder if creating a separate `TestCompilerFactory` is better, but I should be cautious about possible cyclic dependencies. Defining a public static class in `AbstractJavaSourceClassLoaderTest` might work, yet it references other test classes. Modifying `CompilerFactoryFactoryTest.TestCompilerFactory` to implement `JavaSourceClassLoader` could be simpler, allowing `AbstractJavaSourceClassLoaderTest` to use that factory, keeping accessibility in mind.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Inspecting constraints and modifications**\\\\n\\\\nI see that I need to inspect the constraints and check the style for a public class. The existing Commons_compilerTest has a package-private element that violates the requirement for all top-level classes to be public. I’m thinking I shouldn’t modify that directly. I also need to consider adding an import for 'File' and reading the ICompilerFactory interface. It's all about ensuring everything aligns with the current standards without making unnecessary changes!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_2M2Bu47XvDvj26dGp9Hw10X1|fc_00cbef746c3021890169f93d7ed54481949fe1473229c10f37\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge9/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.codehaus.janino/commons-compiler/3.0.16/main/extracted/org/codehaus/commons/compiler/ICompilerFactory.java\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1615, \"output\": 1047, \"cacheRead\": 13312, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 15974, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777941868970, \"responseId\": \"resp_00cbef746c3021890169f93d6d51dc8194b6862744338dbdce\"}}\n1420:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating test modifications**\\n\\nI'm considering whether to modify `CompilerFactoryFactoryTest` to avoid caching the default since it calls `getDefault`, which can't be reset. Editing existing tests could help sidestep this, yet it might affect coverage. Replacing the call to default could work, but I'm also thinking about keeping tests independent of method order with `@TestMethodOrder`. Maybe merging all context default tests into one factory is an option? A shared factory class could be more robust for both tests.\\n\\n**Considering test architecture**\\n\\nI'm pondering whether to place a shared factory in the new `AbstractJavaSourceClassLoaderTest`, which could allow for existing references. I wonder if creating a separate `TestCompilerFactory` is better, but I should be cautious about possible cyclic dependencies. Defining a public static class in `AbstractJavaSourceClassLoaderTest` might work, yet it references other test classes. Modifying `CompilerFactoryFactoryTest.TestCompilerFactory` to implement `JavaSourceClassLoader` could be simpler, allowing `AbstractJavaSourceClassLoaderTest` to use that factory, keeping accessibility in mind.\\n\\n**Inspecting constraints and modifications**\\n\\nI see that I need to inspect the constraints and check the style for a public class. The existing Commons_compilerTest has a package-private element that violates the requirement for all top-level classes to be public. I’m thinking I shouldn’t modify that directly. I also need to consider adding an import for 'File' and reading the ICompilerFactory interface. It's all about ensuring everything aligns with the current standards without making unnecessary changes!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_00cbef746c3021890169f93d6de494819483a114f7bd03b8c0\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-T1-llzGd9g8zycW6bRh1V9AlKnzgHzlJ3-mGaWsm81cQfSHEpjUYkagttFz5PN8Mx3